metadata.name: Tesseract  #24
metadata.description:
Reconfiguring the idea of the cube, the artefact, the platonic solid that is both a rectangle and a hexagon depending on the observer location. This 'interactive' piece explores the multiplicities that can originate from such a simple shape using procedural techniques. Feel free to drag and play around with your own personalised tesseract.

Variations can be explored on pressing the following keys on the keyboard:
'2','3','4','5','6','7','8','9'
Hit '1' to reset.

The artwork is currently set to render at a default 24fps. Change the fps by pressing the following keys. However it is also hardware dependant
Press 'i' - 24fps
Press 'o' - 60fps
Press 'p' - 120fps 

Each iteration is driven by the unique hash associated with each peice that you can mint which effectively drives 
- the number of instances of the cube 
- the size and density of the core cluster 
- the superimposed skeletal wireframe of the base mesh

metadata.name: Happenings #36
metadata.description:
Inspired by the chaos and imperfectly beautiful dynamics of parenting and life, 'Happenings' is the embodiment of the messiness, the unexpected and playful experiences that allow for the greatest depths of connection with our children.

Our intention was to evoke our deepest and most personal feelings as parents of young ones navigating the challenges of the pandemic while immersing ourselves in the Web3 arena.

This collection is Jimena + Marcos’ first generative art collection in the Tezos blockchain via FX Hash, and consists of 222 1/1 artworks created with javascript.

metadata.name: ION TRAP #72
metadata.description:
Inside the ION TRAP, reality is suspended. Particles hang motionless, captured in a glowing web of energy that hums with an endless, static resonance. Time has ceased to flow, frozen in a tension where neither motion nor decay is possible. The trap's design reflects the peak of retro-futuristic ambition; crafted to transcend the very limits of nature. It stands as a testament to the brilliance — and the final misstep — of a civilization that sought to master the fabric of existence, only to unwittingly freeze their world forever.

***

Press ⬅️➡️ to rotate scene.

Press [1/2/4/6/8/0] to change resolution to 1/2/4/6/8/10K along the short edge. 

Press [s] to save a png at the current resolution. Saving at higher resolutions may not work on all browsers (tested: all resolutions work using Safari on an M2 mac. Up to 4K work on Chrome). 

Press [p] to restart the draw animation and initiate download of png frames at current resolution until drawing is complete. Typically generates 500-600 images. Can be assembled into a video / GIF with your software of choice. Recommend doing this at 2K resolution.

100% code generative artwork written in javascript using the p5.js library.

Bleaker 2024

metadata.name: MOMENT #244
metadata.description:
An endless row of them making up each life. Some poignant, some inspiring, some grievous, some affirming - but most of them a tad boring, a bit generic, almost forgettable like bland fabric. How can a life constructed from such mundanity count for anything? Maybe thanks to the last one, the one that stitches them all together, like a punchline to an absurdist joke.

Generative art written in JavaScript + Canvas with a little bit of help from p5.js.

metadata.name: Ordered Chaos #15
metadata.description:
Ordered Chaos is a dynamic interplay of precision and distortion, where structure and movement converge to form a captivating visual symphony. The artwork unfolds as a mosaic of geometric grids, vibrant hues, and flowing deformations, creating a sense of controlled entropy.

Bold colors—emerald greens, electric blues, fiery reds, and glowing yellows—dominate the composition, their contrasts breathing life into each segment. Rigid, orderly grids anchor the piece, yet these are disrupted by undulating lines and warped forms, suggesting an unseen force bending structure into fluidity.

The composition balances tension and harmony. Some sections radiate stability, showcasing clean, linear patterns, while others twist and contort, evoking motion and transformation. These distortions ripple across the surface, connecting the fragmented forms into a single cohesive flow—where chaos is not destruction but evolution.

Ordered Chaos reflects the duality of modern existence: a world shaped by digital precision and organic spontaneity. It invites viewers to immerse themselves in its patterns, to see order and disorder as two sides of the same whole, and to embrace the beauty that emerges when the two coexist in perfect tension.

metadata.name: Warped #18
metadata.description:
A free little toy.  Play with it and it might make art!  This is my second project using a shader.  It starts by making a simple drawing, then the shader uses noise to warp the image.  I'm making it free because 1) You really have to work at it to make art (but I think it's a lot of fun to tinker with!), and 2) the capture sometimes has minor variances from the final image - couldn't figure it out.  Made with p5js and uses some Perlin noise code by Inigo Quilez.  

After opening, press "s" to save a large jpg.
